## Verify Your Understanding

Before looking at the final code, test yourself. These questions check whether you understand the game or just followed steps.

<Challenge>

**Question 1:** Without looking at your code, list the three PICO-8 functions that form the game loop and describe when each one runs.

</Challenge>

<Challenge>

**Question 2:** The game uses tables for bullets and enemies. Explain why a table is necessary - what would go wrong with a single variable?

</Challenge>

<Challenge>

**Question 3:** Collision detection checks `abs(b.x-e.x)<6 and abs(b.y-e.y)<6`. In your own words, what does this line do? Why `and` instead of `or`?

</Challenge>

<Challenge>

**Question 4:** What does the `return` keyword do at the top of _update() when game_over is true? What would happen without it?

</Challenge>

If you can answer all four confidently, you understand the game. If any feel shaky, go back and reread that section.

