## Quick Reference

### Buttons

| Code | Action |
|------|--------|
| `btn(0)` | left |
| `btn(1)` | right |
| `btn(2)` | up |
| `btn(3)` | down |
| `btn(4)` | Z |
| `btn(5)` | X |
| `btnp(n)` | pressed this frame only |

### Drawing

| Code | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `cls()` | clear screen |
| `spr(n,x,y)` | draw sprite |
| `pset(x,y,c)` | draw pixel |
| `print(s,x,y,c)` | draw text |
| `circfill(x,y,r,c)` | filled circle |
| `rectfill(x,y,x2,y2,c)` | filled rectangle |

### PICO-8 Colors

| | |
|---|---|
| 0 black | 8 red |
| 1 dark blue | 9 orange |
| 2 dark purple | 10 yellow |
| 3 dark green | 11 green |
| 4 brown | 12 blue |
| 5 dark grey | 13 indigo |
| 6 light grey | 14 pink |
| 7 white | 15 peach |

### Math Helpers

| Code | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `rnd(n)` | random 0 to n |
| `flr(n)` | floor |
| `abs(n)` | absolute value |
| `min(a,b)` | smaller value |
| `max(a,b)` | larger value |

---

The PICO-8 manual is built in. Type `help` at the console prompt, or read it online: [lexaloffle.com/dl/docs/pico-8_manual.html](https://lexaloffle.com/dl/docs/pico-8_manual.html)
